1 (2) A wholly owned subsidiary of an entity described in subdivision (1) of this
2 subsection.
3 (3) The State or any political subdivision of the State.
4 (4) Institutions of higher education, as defined in G.S. 116-143.1.
5 (5) College Foundation, Inc.
6 (6) Eligible private postsecondary institutions, as defined in G.S. 116-280.
7 (7) Organizations, as described in 26 U.S.C. § 509(a)(1), (2), or (3), that support
8 the work of institutions of higher education and eligible private postsecondary
9 institutions exempted by this subsection.
10 "§ 53-444. License application.
11 (a) Application. – Applications under this Article shall be filed through the Nationwide
12 Multistate Licensing System and Registry (NMLS) in a form acceptable to the Commissioner.
13 To be considered complete, the application shall be verified by attestation of the applicant or a
14 designee of the applicant and shall include all of the following:
15 (1) The applicant's legal name, along with any assumed business name, principal
16 address, including street address and mailing address, contact information,
17 and social security number or taxpayer identification number.
18 (2) The applicant's form and place of organization, if applicable.
19 (3) A certificate of good standing from the state in which the applicant was
20 organized, if applicable.
21 (4) A certificate of authority from the North Carolina Secretary of State to
22 conduct business in this State, if required by Article 15 of Chapter 55 of the
23 General Statutes, or other evidence of the applicant's registration or
24 qualification to do business in this State.
25 (5) The qualifications and business history of the applicant and, if applicable, the
26 business history of any person controlling the applicant, including a
27 description of any injunction or administrative order by any state or federal
28 authority to which the person is or has been subject.
29 (6) The applicant's financial condition, including its credit history, business
30 history, and most recent audited annual financial statement or, if the applicant
31 is a wholly owned subsidiary, the most recent audited annual financial
32 statement of the applicant's parent entity. This statement shall include the
33 balance sheet, statement of income or loss, statement of changes in
34 shareholder equity, if applicable, and statement of changes in financial
35 position.
36 (7) A record of any criminal convictions for the applicant or, in the case of an
37 applicant that is an entity, each individual who has control of the applicant for
38 a 10-year period prior to the date of the application, including the applicant's
39 consent to a federal and State criminal background check and a set of the
40 applicant's fingerprints in a form acceptable to the Commissioner. In the case
41 of an applicant that is an entity, each individual who has control over the
42 applicant shall consent to a federal and State criminal background check and
43 shall submit a set of the individual's fingerprints.
44 (8) A current schedule of the ranges and categories of the fees it charges
45 borrowers for servicing student loans.
46 (9) Any additional information that the Commissioner deems relevant.
47 (b) Fees. – An applicant shall include a nonrefundable application fee of one thousand
48 five hundred dollars ($1,500) with the application. In addition, every applicant for initial
49 licensure shall pay the actual cost of obtaining a credit report and federal and State criminal
50 background checks and the processing fees required by the NMLS.
DRS45219-MUf-38 Page 3

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (c) Investigation. – On receipt of the application and fees, the Commissioner shall
2 investigate the applicant's financial condition and responsibility, financial and business
3 experience, and character and general fitness.
4 (d) Abandoned Application. – The Commissioner may deem an application abandoned if
5 the applicant fails to respond to a written request for information by the Commissioner within 30
6 days of the date of the request. The written request may be given to the applicant through the
7 NMLS or by other electronic means.
8 (e) Issuance of License. – The Commissioner shall issue a student loan servicer license
9 to an applicant if the Commissioner finds all of the following:
10 (1) The applicant has satisfied the requirements imposed by this Article.
11 (2) The applicant's business will be conducted honestly, fairly, and in a manner
12 commanding the confidence and trust of the community.
13 (3) The applicant has demonstrated net worth necessary to satisfy the
14 requirements of G.S. 53-445.
15 (4) The applicant has obtained a surety bond in conformance with G.S. 53-446.
16 (5) Persons controlling the applicant, as a group, have degrees of character,
17 competence, and experience that command the confidence and trust of the
18 community and justify the belief that the applicant will operate safely,
19 soundly, and in compliance with the law.
20 (6) The applicant meets other similar requirements determined by the
21 Commissioner.
22 (f) Automatic Issuance of License for Federal Student Loan Servicing Contractors. – A
23 person seeking to act within this State as a student loan servicer is exempt from the procedures
24 described in subsections (a) through (d) of this section upon a determination by the Commissioner
25 that the person is a party to a contract awarded by the United States Secretary of Education under
26 20 U.S.C. § 1087f. Any person seeking this exemption shall submit a written request for
27 verification of exemption to the Commissioner. The request shall be in a form acceptable to the
28 Commissioner and shall include a copy of any written agreement and related documentation that
29 is the basis for the exemption. The following provisions apply to the exemption:
30 (1) Actions by Commissioner. – With regard to a person deemed exempt under
31 this subsection, the Commissioner shall do both of the following:
32 a. Automatically issue a license upon payment of the fees required by
33 subsection (b) of this section.
34 b. Automatically issue a renewal license upon payment of the assessment
35 required by G.S. 53-448.
36 (2) Notice. – A person issued a license pursuant to this subsection shall provide
37 the Commissioner with written notice within seven days after notification of
38 the expiration, revocation, or termination of any contract awarded by the
39 United States Secretary of Education under 20 U.S.C. § 1087f. The person has
40 30 days after notification to satisfy all requirements established under
41 subsections (a) and (b) of this section in order to continue to act within this
42 State as a student loan servicer. At the expiration of the 30-day period, if the
43 person seeking to act within this State as a student loan servicer has not
44 satisfied the requirements of subsections (a) and (b) of this section, the
45 Commissioner shall summarily suspend any license granted to the person
46 under this section.
47 (3) Preservation of authorities. – With respect to student loan servicing not
48 conducted pursuant to a contract awarded by the United States Secretary of
49 Education under 20 U.S.C. § 1087f, nothing in this section prevents the
50 Commissioner from issuing, or filing a civil action for, an order to temporarily
