1 (10) Make any false statement or omit any material fact in connection with
2 information or reports filed with a governmental agency or in connection with
3 an investigation or examination conducted by the Commissioner.
4 (11) Communicate with a borrower in any manner designed to harass or intimidate
5 the borrower.
6 (12) Violate State or federal privacy laws.
7 "§ 53-452. Commissioner's authority to investigate and examine.
8 (a) For purposes of carrying out this Article, the Commissioner may access any
9 documents or information, including all of the following:
10 (1) Criminal, civil, and administrative history information, including data
11 unrelated to a conviction.
12 (2) Personal history and experience information, including independent credit
13 reports obtained from a consumer reporting agency.
14 (3) Any other documents, information, or evidence the Commissioner deems
15 relevant to the inquiry, investigation, or examination regardless of the
16 location, possession, control, or custody of the documents or information.
17 (b) The Commissioner may investigate or examine any student loan servicer as often as
18 necessary to carry out the purposes of this Article. The Commissioner may interview borrowers,
19 as well as the student loan servicer's controlling persons, employees, independent contractors,
20 and agents. The Commissioner may order the attendance of and examine under oath all persons
21 whose testimony about the student loan servicing activity the Commissioner deems relevant. The
22 Commissioner may also order the student loan servicer to produce documents or information the
23 Commissioner deems relevant. Any investigation or examination that, in the opinion of the
24 Commissioner, requires extraordinary review, investigation, or examination is subject to the
25 actual costs of additional expenses and the hourly rate for the Office of the Commissioner of
26 Banks' staff's time, to be determined annually by the State Banking Commission.
27 (c) Upon request, each student loan servicer shall make available in a location that is
28 acceptable to the Commissioner the records relating to the operations of the student loan servicer.
29 No person shall knowingly withhold, remove, secrete, mutilate, or destroy any records or
30 information. The Commissioner may control access to the records by moving them to another
31 location or placing a person in exclusive charge of them where they are usually kept. During this
32 period of control, no person shall remove any records or information except pursuant to a court
33 order or with the consent of the Commissioner. Unless the Commissioner has a reason to believe
34 the records are at risk of being withheld, removed, secreted, mutilated, or destroyed, the student
35 loan servicer shall have access to them.
36 (d) Each student loan servicer shall make or compile reports as directed by the
37 Commissioner to carry out the purposes of this section, including any of the following:
38 (1) Accounting compilations.
39 (2) Information lists and data concerning student loan servicing activities in a
40 format prescribed by the Commissioner.
41 (3) Periodic reports, including any of the following:
42 a. Annual report questionnaires.
43 b. Any report required by the NMLS.
44 (e) To carry out the purposes of this section, the Commissioner may do any of the
45 following:
46 (1) Retain attorneys, accountants, or other professionals and specialists as
47 examiners, auditors, or investigators to assist with the investigation or
48 examination.
49 (2) Enter into agreements or relationships with other governmental agencies or
50 regulatory associations to improve efficiencies and reduce the regulatory
DRS45219-MUf-38 Page 9

